{"id":"1612.09482","submitter":"Tingting Li","authors":"Tingting Li, Jianlong Chen, Sanzhang Xu","title":"Core and Dual Core Inverses of a Sum of Morphisms","comments":"16 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CT math.RA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Let $\\mathscr{C}$ be an additive category with an involution $\\ast$. Suppose\nthat $\\varphi : X \\rightarrow X$ is a morphism of $\\mathscr{C}$ with core\ninverse $\\varphi^{\\co} : X \\rightarrow X$ and $\\eta : X \\rightarrow X$ is a\nmorphism of $\\mathscr{C}$ such that $1_X+\\varphi^{\\co}\\eta$ is invertible. Let\n$\\alpha=(1_X+\\varphi^{\\co}\\eta)^{-1},$ $\\beta=(1_X+\\eta\\varphi^{\\co})^{-1},$\n$\\varepsilon=(1_X-\\varphi\\varphi^{\\co})\\eta\\alpha(1_X-\\varphi^{\\co}\\varphi),$\n$\\gamma=\\alpha(1_X-\\varphi^{\\co}\\varphi)\\beta^{-1}\\varphi\\varphi^{\\co}\\beta,$\n$\\sigma=\\alpha\\varphi^{\\co}\\varphi\\alpha^{-1}(1_X-\\varphi\\varphi^{\\co})\\beta,$\n$\\delta=\\beta^{\\ast}(\\varphi^{\\co})^{\\ast}\\eta^{\\ast}(1_X-\\varphi\\varphi^{\\co})\\beta.$\nThen $f=\\varphi+\\eta-\\varepsilon$ has a core inverse if and only if\n$1_X-\\gamma$, $1_X-\\sigma$ and $1_X-\\delta$ are invertible. Moreover, the\nexpression of the core inverse of $f$ is presented. Let $R$ be a unital\n$\\ast$-ring and $J(R)$ its Jacobson radical, if $a\\in R^{\\co}$ with core\ninverse $a^{\\co}$ and $j\\in J(R)$, then $a+j\\in R^{\\co}$ if and only if\n$(1-aa^{\\co})j(1+a^{\\co}j)^{-1}(1-a^{\\co}a)=0$. We also give the similar\nresults for the dual core inverse.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Dec 2016 07:37:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-02"}
